description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF Kyrgyzstan built its communication around the 30th anniversary of the Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC). The flagship initiative of the year, echoing the global Cause Framework' campaign ‘End Violence Against Children', was the “Tumar” campaign, conducted under the auspices of the President of Kyrgyzstan to raise awareness on the harmful impact of violent discipline. 10,000 signatures were gathered online to ban corporal punishment. 16 new or renewed partnerships with governmental institutions, civil society and the media served to bring children rights to the public agenda. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/12/2019
